# Checkpoint commit

## Before editing
1. `git status`
2. Uncommitted changes → checkpoint commit first, then start new work.

## After done
1. `git status` + `git diff`
2. Valid changes → commit (unless user says skip). No push unless asked.

## Message (Vietnamese)
- Describe **what actually changed**, not vague labels.
- First line = short summary; body optional.

| Bad | Good |
|---|---|
| `fix`, `update` | `Sửa crash load native trên arm64` |
| `WIP` | `Thêm clean task xóa .cxx và externalNativeBuild` |

## Never commit
`local.properties`, `*.jks`, `*.keystore`, `.env`, secrets, build/cache dirs (see `.gitignore`).
